[{"name":"Using hasNext()","code":"```
String s = "Hello, This is Scanner.";  

//Create scanner Object and pass string in it  
Scanner scan = new Scanner(s);  

//Check if the scanner has a token  
System.out.println("Result: " + scan.hasNext());  

//Print the string  
System.out.println("String: " +scan.nextLine());  
```
**Output:**
Result: true 
String: Hello, This is Scanner."}]

[{"name":"Using hasNextBoolean()","description":"","code":"```
 String s = "hello false goodbye!";

//create a new Scanner object with String s
Scanner scanner = new Scanner(s);

        // keep going while there is still input in the Scanner object
        while (scanner.hasNext()) {

            // check if the scanner's next token is a Boolean 
            System.out.print("" + scanner.hasNextBoolean());

            System.out.print(" -> " + scanner.next() + "\n");
        }
        scanner.close();
```
